1507.name: Anubimon

1509.name: Arkadimon (Ultimate)

1509.leader_skill: Reduces the damage received by half.
1509.profile: A Digimon who evolved to an Ultimate form by absorbing dark data. It can also achieve the Ultimate evolution through its tamer, and when not controlled by its tamer, it can transform into various other forms.

1510.name: Mistymon

1510.leader_skill: Only yellow holy cards will appear next.
1510.profile: A Digimon who has mastered many magical skills (advanced programming languages) and is also quite skilled at swordplay.

1511.name: Boogiemon

1511.leader_skill: Inflicts a small amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.

1512.name: Darklizamon
1512.main_skill: High increase in the attack power of purple dark allies.
1512.profile: An Evil Dragon Digimon with its whole body covered in a quietly burning dark flame. It is a virus evolved from Flarelizamon with a cool personality.

1513.name: Phelesmon
1513.main_skill: Reduces the damage received by half.
1513.leader_skill: Inflicts a large amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.

1514.leader_skill: High decrease in the attack power of all enemies.
1514.profile: A Flame Dragon Digimon with its whole body covered in flames. Hot-blooded, it possesses a burning heart and the power of a dragon.

1515.leader_skill: Damages all enemies while your HP drops to 1.
1515.profile: A Digimon that manages all time and space within the computers on the Network. It can freely move back and forth in time, at least within the years 1900-1999.

1516.name: Mametyramon

1516.leader_skill: Reduces the damage received from green nature enemies.
1516.profile: A small Mutant Digimon feared as the 'Little Tyrant'. It is comprised of Tyranomon's data condensed into a tiny body, and despite its appearance, Tyranomon's ferocity and combat instincts are remarkably recognizable.

1517.name: Ex-tyranomon
1517.main_skill: Inflicts medium damage to all enemies.

1517.profile: A Puppet Digimon that sneaked its way inside a stuffed animal in the shape of Tyranomon.

1518.name: Igamon

1518.profile: A mysterious Digimon wearing a red mask. It wanders through the Digital World accumulating knowledge.

1519.name: Kougamon

1521.profile: It is said to be the Digimon form of the wicked wolf who appears in all the fairy tales. Once it has selected his prey, it never lets it escape. Sometimes it even masquerades as a friend of its prey in order to get close to them.

1537.name: Werewolf's grain

1538.name: Werewolf's crystal

1539.name: Light of God

1540.name: Raijinmon

1540.leader_skill: High decrease in the attack power of all enemies.
1540.profile: A Cyborg Digimon with the name of 'Raijin', the thunder god of Eastern mythology. It is very adept at close combat.

1541.name: Fujinmon

1541.leader_skill: Changes the value of all cards to 9.
1541.profile: A Cyborg Digimon with the name of 'Fujin', the wind god of Eastern mythology. A light fighter who uses airy movements, it is skilled at close combat.

1542.name: Suijinmon

1542.profile: A Machine Digimon made of parts of Mugendramon and Justimon.

1548.name: Anomalocarimon

1548.leader_skill: The green nature cards will not appear.

1550.name: Waspmon

1550.leader_skill: Inflicts a large amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.

1551.name: Tobucatmon

1553.name: Eldoradimon
1553.main_skill: Inflicts a small amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.
1553.leader_skill: Inflict a large amount of damage to one enemy.
1553.profile: A Mutant Digimon born when a Digimon became lost in the ancient ruins of abandoned computers and eventually fused with the research data stored there.

1554.name: Raidenmon
1554.main_skill: Small increase in the defense of all allies.
1554.leader_skill: Medium increase in the defense power of blue knight allies.
1554.profile: A heavyweight Machine Digimon equipped with electromagnetic firing weapons.

1555.leader_skill: High increase in the attack power of blue knight allies.
1555.profile: A Powered Suit Digimon. It is run by a small Digimon inside it. A Digimon still under development, its digicore can cause overheating depending on the operating conditions.

1556.name: Blimpmon

1556.leader_skill: Inflicts a large amount of damage to all enemies.
1556.profile: The soft balloon-like section of this Digimon is covered by a metal coating, but apparently it is still under development, as the left half of its body is left bare.

1557.leader_skill: Inflict most of the damage to one enemy.

1558.name: Chaosdramon

1558.leader_skill: Only blue knight cards will appear next.

1580.name: Witchmon

1580.leader_skill: Changes all the brown recovery cards in purple dark cards.

1581.name: Dogmon

1582.name: Starmon

1596.name: Pumpmon

1596.profile: An upbeat Digimon born on Halloween through the variation of a virus. It has a calm personality and avoids initiating hostilities, but its appearance belies its formidable abilities.

1622.leader_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 1.
1622.profile: A Digimon with no attack power or intelligence, it prefers dark, dank environments. If raised incorrectly, it's liable to turn into a Numemon, but they say it actually conceals a hidden secret...

1623.name: Karatukinumemon
1623.main_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 1.
1623.leader_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 1.
1623.profile: A subspecies of Numemon born when a Numemon entered a shell and became a snail.

1625.leader_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 1.
1625.profile: A subspecies of Numemon with a golden body. It was born when a Numemon discovered Goldine mine and incorporated elements from it.

1626.name: Platinum Numemon
1626.main_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 2.
1626.leader_skill: Medium decrease in the attack power of all enemies.
1626.profile: An extremely rare subspecies of Numemon. It was born when a Numemon was the first in the Digital World to discover Platina Mine, evolving and incorporating elements from the mine.

1633.profile: A Digimon who jogress-evolved from XV-mon and Stingmon. Although it has the skilled attacks of dragons and the defensive ability of insects, the dragon attributes are a little stronger. It is very loyal and always protects its master.

1634.profile: A Digimon that plays its main theme through the two horns on its shoulders. The tone of its voice, several octaves lower than Gekomon's, imparts a feeling of Tonosama's grandeur.

1636.profile: An Aquatic Digimon with a long body, like a big snake. It uses this long body and coils tightly around its enemy until it stops breathing.

1658.name: Qinglongmon

1658.leader_skill: Medium increase in the attack power of all allies.

1659.profile: An eight-headed Digimon. While its primary head in the center is black, the rest of its heads are camouflage. It was born in the ancient Digital World with the purpose of preserving harmony.

1660.leader_skill: Changes all the brown recovery cards in red dragon cards.

1661.name: Blackmegalogrowmon

1667.name: Gigaseadramon

1668.leader_skill: Changes the value of all cards to 9.

1686.name: Babamon

1686.profile: Rumor has it that this Digimon resulted when a curse was cast upon a Rosemon.

1687.name: Leviamon

1687.profile: One of the Seven Great Demon Lords sleeping in the abyss of the Digital World. It has a huge body and is called the Devil Beast due to its very large jaw.

1688.name: Kyukimon
1688.main_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 2.
1688.leader_skill: Medium increase in the attack power of all allies.
1688.profile: A Bewitching Beast Digimon that looks like a kamaitachi. Its whole body is like a sharp blade that indiscriminately cuts everything in its vicinity.

1691.profile: A Dragon Man Digimon gifted with fighting skills. It lives in unexplored territory and hunts down its enemies with its sword, Akinakes.

1692.leader_skill: Inflicts a small amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.
1692.profile: A Digimon feared as the 'White Devil of the Deep Seas'. It is very intelligent and does no harm to Digimon outside of its territory.

1693.leader_skill: Changes all the brown recovery cards in purple dark cards.
1693.profile: A Digimon that treats everything it sees and touches as an object of its hatred. It chants magic in a lost, ancient high-level programming language.

1695.name: Manbomon
1695.main_skill: Medium increase in the defense of all allies.
1695.leader_skill: Medium increase in the support power of all allies.
1695.profile: An Armor-body Mutant Digimon that evolved through the power of the 'Digimental of Light'. Highly rare, it is scarcely seen in the Network seas.

1696.name: Jijimon

1700.profile: One of the 'Deva Digimon', this one is a Perfect form in the shape of a boar.

1771.leader_skill: Increases the value of all cards by 1.
1771.profile: This Digimon loves peace and doesn't especially care for combat. However, it conceals many latent hidden powers, and when it fights to protect someone, its actual combat abilities are exceptional.

1777.name: Rinkmon

1777.leader_skill: Only brown recovery cards will appear next.
1777.profile: A Cyborg Digimon born from the sample data of an experiment that accelerated particles to the speed of light in a particle accelerator.

1778.name: Hyougamon

1778.leader_skill: Restores a small portion of your HP.
1778.profile: A species of Ogremon that lives in cold places. It is highly protective of its territory and angrily attacks any Digimon who dare take one step into it.

1781.leader_skill: Inflicts medium damage to all enemies.
1781.profile: A half-beast-half-human Digimon, it uses his tentacles for both attack and defense, spinning them to attack its enemies or retracting them to protect its body.

1783.profile: A subspecies of Digimon. It is full of hatred because it lives alone in the deep sea. Its two tentacles have their own will and are free to attack on their own.

1784.name: Raremon

1784.leader_skill: Only attack cards will appear next.

1785.name: Kaisergreymon
1785.main_skill: Inflicts a small amount of damage and restore the same amount of HP.
1785.leader_skill: Inflict a large amount of damage to one enemy.
1785.profile: A transcendent species of Digimon that possesses fire powers and is said to surpass the power of even the legendary Ten Warriors.

1787.name: Phelesmon

1808.name: Dynasmon

1808.leader_skill: Inflict most of the damage to one enemy.

1883.name: Knowledge of the Steel Knights

1985.name: Griffomon
1985.main_skill: Medium decrease in the attack power of all enemies.
1985.profile: A Synthetic Digimon with a Beast's torso and a Bird's head, wings, and legs. There is something like a snake attached to his tail.

1986.name: Hippogriffomon
1986.main_skill: Strong chance to instantly kill one enemy.
1986.leader_skill: Reduces the damage received by half.
1986.profile: A Mythical Beast Digimon in the shape of a synthetic beast. It is said it evolves into Griffomon, but further details are unknown.

1990.name: Unimon
1990.main_skill: Changes all the red dragon cards in brown recovery cards.
1990.profile: A synthetic Digimon with a unicorn's horn and a pegasus' wings. Its wings help it fly freely within the network, and its sharp horn helps it fight its enemies. It has a very wild temper.
